<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Connect to OneNote</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <!-- You can replace this with your actual logo -->
      <img src="/images/logo.png" alt="App Logo" style="max-width: 150px; margin-bottom: 20px;">

      <h1>Connect Your Microsoft Account</h1>
      <p>
        To automatically load your latest OneNote notebooks, our
        application needs to connect to your OneNote account.
      </p>

      <div class="permission-list">
        <p>By authorizing, you allow our application to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>✅ Read all OneNote notebooks that you can access.</li>
          <li>✅ Maintain access to data you have given it access to, even when you're not actively using the application.</li>
          <li>✅ Sign you in and read your basic user profile information.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <a href="/partner/authorize" class="cta-button"
        >Authorize Access to OneNote</a
      >
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
